actual.comment:
1. Thematic working group on GHG inventory system and national dialogue platforms and coordination mechanisms partially in place. The National Inventory Strategy was finalized. The institutionalization of the data collection system is partially in place. The QA/QC framework is in place and outlined in the strategy. Capacity building is on-going to allow for a fully institutionalized and government owned QA/QC system. The GHG unit is operational and capacity is in place to manage the inventory;

2. Four Nationally Appropriate Mitigation Actions (NAMA) full proposals are under construction. Business models for the four NAMAs are under construction;

3. MRV for GHG inventory systems and NAMAs partially in place. Rules of procedures are part of the GHG inventory strategy

1. Sixteen ALD staff supported to attend training in ODA management related courses
2. Functional Monitoring mechanism for aid coordination and management in place. Development partner data reconciled for annual ODA reporting;
3. Annual Portfolio review of UNDP projects conducted, report in place; Eleven (11) projects audited according to audit plan, audit results presented, action plans put in place and being implemented. Two (2) International events supported on ODA best practices (Climate change Financing/Conference, Tokyo International conference on African Development) and reports are in place 4. UNDAF review and Annual CPAP evaluation completed

1. National Consultative Forum (NCF) fully operational with key capacities to deliver on constitutional mandate. Specifically 17 electoral reform proposals under this forum were finalized and cleared by cabinet for 2016 elections; Political party dialogues were held including presidential political debates;

2. A legislation associated with electoral processes and multiparty political dispensation in place.

3. Operational Non-state dialogue platform in place.  A functional National Elders Forum is in place;

4.  Policy and governance settlements have been facilitated by Non-structures (NEF and in close conjunction with NCF and IRCU) 

5. Regional peace and conflict transformation forums are in place- addressing dialogue and internal mediation in diffusing conflict triggers at regional levels

6. There is the existence of Independent and impartial secretariat for the operations of the NEF/NCF/IRCU.

1. Three data innovation projects completed and used to advocate for a global partnership to tap into the data revolution to advance/monitor SDGs. 

2: 3 data innovation projects completed and used to advance/monitor SDGs;

3: 3 advocacy events conducted in Kampala advocating for the data revolution to advance/monitor SDGs.

Target 1:

The capacity assessment scorecard is divided into four different categories of indicators and for transparency purposes the progress will be presented as per the four categories: 


1) Capacity of Agencies to produce information: An increase from the baseline 33 to 40 (project target is 51) representing 38% based on the score cars rating;

2) Capacity of Agencies to package information: Too early to capture progress for this category;

3) Capacity of Agencies to disseminate information: Increase from 20 to 25 (project target is 40) representing 20% based on the score card;

4) Capacity of Legislative and Governance framework: An increase from 7 to 9 (project target is 9) representing 22 % based on the scorecard


The overall progress is 14 points equivalent to 9.1%  (the baseline is 77 and the project target 143). 


Target 2:

There was an increase in domestic finance from 1,482,193 USD (in the financial year June 2014-June 2015)  to 3,590,486 USD (in the financial year June 2015-June 2016) representing over 100% increase.
